obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (32689)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32689&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the State Bank of Sikkim`
  line `(Acquisition of Shares) and Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1982.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (32690)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32690&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the date on which this Act comes into force;`
  line
  line `(b) "co-operative bank" means the Sikkim State Co-operative Bank Limited, a society registered`
  line `under the Sikkim Co-operative Societies Act, 1978 (Sikkim Act No. 12 of 1978);`
  line
  line `(c) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(d) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "Sikkim Bank" means the State Bank of Sikkim constituted under the State Bank of Sikkim`
  line `Proclamation, 1968;`
  line
  line `(f) "State Government" means the State Government of Sikkim;`
  line
  line `(g) "United Commercial Bank" means the United Commercial Bank constituted under section 3`
  line `of the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings)Act, 1970 (5 of 1970);`
  line
  line `(h) words and expressions used herein and not defined but defined in the Companies Act, 1956`
  line `(1 of 1956), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (32691)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Vesting in the Central Government of certain shares of Sikkim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32691&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the appointed`
  line `day, all the shares in the share capital of the State Bank of Sikkim, other than the shares held by the State`
  line `Government, shall, by virtue of this Act, stand transferred to, and shall vest in, the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) All the shares which have vested in the Central Government under sub-section (1) shall, by force`
  line `of such vesting, be freed and discharged of all trusts, liabilities, obligations, mortgages, charges, liens and`
  line `other encumbrances affecting them, and any attachment or injunction or any decree or order of any court,`
  line `tribunal or other authority restricting the use of such shares in any manner shall be deemed to have been`
  line withdrawn.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding the transfer of the shares of the Sikkim Bank to the Central Government under`
  line `sub-section (1), any person holding such shares, who immediately before the appointed day is entitled to`
  line `payment of dividend on such shares, shall be entitled to receive from the co-operative bank--`
  line
  line `(a) all dividends accruing due on his shares in respect of the half-year which ended before the`
  line `appointed day and remaining unpaid;`
  line
  line `(b) dividends calculated at a rate to be specified by the Central Government in respect of any`
  line `period immediately preceding the appointed day for which the Sikkim Bank had not declared any`
  line dividend.
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (32692)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Vesting of undertaking of Sikkim Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32692&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On the appointed day, the undertakings of the Sikkim`
  line `Bank shall, by virtue of this Act, stand transferred to, and shall vest in, the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (32693)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `General effect of vesting.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32693&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The undertakings of the Sikkim Bank shall be deemed to include`
  line `all assets, rights, powers, authorities and privileges, and all property, movable and immovable, cash`
  line `balances, reserve funds, investments and all other rights and interests in, or arising out of, such property`
  line `as were immediately before the appointed day in the ownership, possession, power or control of the`
  line `Sikkim Bank in relation to its undertakings, and all books of account, registers, records and all other`
  line `documents of whatever nature relating thereto and shall also be deemed to include all borrowings,`
  line `liabilities and obligations of whatever kind then subsisting of the Sikkim Bank in relation to its`
  line undertakings.
  line
  line `(2) Unless otherwise expressly provided in this Act, all contracts, deeds, bonds, agreements, powers`
  line `of attorney, grants of legal representation and other instruments of whatever nature subsisting or having`
  line `effect immediately before the appointed day and to which the Sikkim Bank is a party or which are in`
  line `favour of the said Bank shall be of as full force and effect against or in favour of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) If, on the appointed day, any suit, appeal or other proceeding of whatever nature in relation to any`
  line `business of the undertakings which have been transferred under section 4 is pending by or against the`
  line `Sikkim Bank, the same shall not abate, be discontinued, or be in any way prejudicially affected by reason`
  line `of the transfer of the undertakings of the Sikkim Bank or of anything contained in this Act, but the suit,`
  line `appeal or other proceeding may be continued, prosecuted or enforced by or against the Central`
  line Government.
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (32694)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Vesting of the shares and undertakings of Sikkim Bank in the State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32694&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 3, 4 and 5, the Central Government shall, as soon as may`
  line `be, after the commencement of this Act, direct, by notification, that the shares of the Sikkim Bank which`
  line `have vested in the Central Government under section 3 and the undertakings of the Sikkim Bank which`
  line `have vested in the Central Government under section 4 shall, instead of continuing to vest in the Central`
  line `Government, vest in the State Government of Sikkim, on the date of the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the shares and the undertakings of the Sikkim Bank vest In the State Government under`
  line `sub-section (1), the State Government shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to have`
  line `become the owner in relation to such shares and undertakings and all the rights and liabilities of the`
  line `Central Government in relation to such shares and undertakings shall, on and from the date of such`
  line `vesting, be deemed to have become the rights and liabilities, respectively, of the State Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (32695)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power of State Government to direct vesting of the undertakings of Sikkim Bank the Sikkim Co-operative bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32695&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 4, 5 and 6, the State`
  line `Government may, if it is satisfied that the co-operative bank is willing to comply, or has complied, with`
  line `such terms and conditions as that Government may think fit to impose, including the terms and conditions`
  line `regarding allotment of its shares, direct, by notification, that the undertakings of the Sikkim Bank which`
  line `have vested in the Central Government under section 4 and thereafter in the State Government under`
  line `section 6, shall, instead of continuing to vest in the State Government, vest in the co-operative bank either on the date of the notification or on such earlier or later date (not being a date earlier than the appointed`
  line `day) as maybe specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the undertakings of the Sikkim Bank vest in the co-operative bank under sub-section (1),`
  line `that bank shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to have become the owner in relation to`
  line `such undertakings, and all the rights and liabilities of the Central Government or the State Government in`
  line `relation to such undertakings shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to have become the`
  line `rights and liabilities, respectively, of the co-operative bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (32696)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Payment of amounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32696&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1)For the transfer to, and vesting in, the Central Government, of the`
  line `shares of the Sikkim Bank under section 3, there shall be given by the Central Government to the holders`
  line `of such shares in cash and in the manner specified in the Schedule, an amount of rupees eight lakhs`
  line `twelve thousand two hundred and ninety-five.`
  line
  line `(2)The amount specified in sub-section (1) shall carry simple interest at the rate of five and a half per`
  line `cent. per annum for the period commencing on the appointed day and ending on the date on which`
  line `payment of such amount is made to the shareholders.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (32697)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Management, etc., of the undertakings of Sikkim Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32697&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government in which`
  line `the undertakings of the Sikkim Bank have vested under section 6 shall be entitled to exercise all such`
  line `powers and do all such things as the Sikkim Bank is authorised to exercise and do in relation to its`
  line undertakings.
  line
  line `(2) The general superintendence, direction, control and management of the affairs and business of the`
  line `undertakings of the Sikkim Bank which have vested under section 4 in the Central Government and under`
  line `section 6in the State Government shall, where a direction has been made by the State Government under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 7, vest in the co-operative bank specified in such direction, and, thereupon, the`
  line `co-operative bank shall be entitled to exercise all such powers and do all such things as the Sikkim Bank`
  line `is authorised to exercise and do in relation to its undertakings.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (42835)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Date of delivery, possession of property acquired and documents relating thereto.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=42835&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) On`
  line `the vesting of the undertakings of the Sikkim Bank in the State Government under section 6, every person`
  line `in whose possession or custody or under whose control any property referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 5 may be, shall deliver the property to the State Government forthwith.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person, who, on the appointed day, has in his possession or under his control any books,`
  line `documents or other papers relating to the undertakings of the Sikkim Bank which have vested in the State`
  line `Government under section 6 and which belong to that Bank, or would have so belonged if the`
  line `undertakings of the Sikkim Bank had not vested in the State Government, shall be liable to account for`
  line `the said books, documents or other papers to the State Government and shall deliver them up to the State`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) The State Government may take, or cause to be taken, all necessary steps for securing possession`
  line `of all properties which have vested in that Government under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (32698)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Transfer of service of existing officers and employees of the Sikkim Bank to the co-operative bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32698&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every officer or other employee of the Sikkim Bank (excepting the Managing Director`
  line `thereof) in the employment of the Sikkim Bank immediately before the appointed day shall become,--`
  line
  line `(a) an officer or other employee of the State Government on any from the appointed day, and`
  line
  line `(b) where the undertakings of the Sikkim Bank are directed, under sub-section (1) of section 7, to`
  line `vest in the co-operative bank, an officer or other employee of the co-operative bank on and from the`
  line `date of such vesting,`
  line
  line `and shall hold his office or service under the State Government or the co-operative bank, as the case may`
  line `be, with the same rights and privileges as to pension, gratuity and other matters as would have been`
  line `admissible to him if there had been no such vesting and shall continue to do so unless and until his`
  line `employment under the State Government or the co-operative bank, as the case may be, is duly terminated`
  line `or until his remuneration and other conditions of service are duly altered by the State Government, or by`
  line `the co-operative bank, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who, on the appointed day, is entitled to, or is intercept of, a pension or other`
  line `superannuation or compassionate allowance or benefit from the Sikkim Bank or any provident fund,`
  line `pension or other fund or any authority administering such fund shall be entitled to be paid by, and to`
  line `receive from, the co-operative bank or any provident fund, pension or other fund or any authority`
  line `administering such fund, the same pension, allowance or benefit so long as he observes the conditions on`
  line `which the pension, allowance or benefit was granted, and if any question arises as to whether he has so`
  line `observed such conditions, the question shall be determined by the State Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), no appointment made or`
  line `promotion, increment in salary, pension allowance or any other benefit granted to any person after the`
  line `16th day of November, 1976, and before the appointed day which would not ordinarily have been made`
  line `or granted or which would not ordinarily have been admissible under the rules or authorisations of the`
  line `Sikkim Bank or of any provident fund or other fund in force prior to the 16th day of November, 1976,`
  line `shall have effect or be payable or claimable from the co-operative bank or from any provident fund,`
  line `pension or other fund or from any authority administering the fund, unless the State Government has, by`
  line `general or special order, confirmed the appointment, promotion or increment, or has directed the`
  line `continued grant of the pension, allowance or other benefit, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Industrial Disputes Act, 1947 (14 of 1947), or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, the transfer of the services of any officer or other employee of the`
  line `Sikkim Bank to the State Government or the co-operative bank shall not entitle such officer or other`
  line `employee to any compensation under that Act or under any other law for the time being in force and no`
  line `such claim shall be entertained by any court, tribunal or other authority.`
  line
  line `(5) Any person holding office as Managing Director of the Sikkim Bank immediately before the`
  line `appointed day shall be deemed to have vacated his office as such on the appointed day and,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this Act or in any other law for the time being in force or in any`
  line `agreement or contract, he shall not be entitled to any amount from the Sikkim Bank, State Government, or`
  line `the co-operative bank for the loss of office or for the premature termination of any agreement or contact`
  line `relating to his employment, except such pension, amount or other benefit which the co-operative bank`
  line `may grant to him, having regard to what that person would have received as an officer of the Sikkim Bank`
  line `if this Act had not been passed and if he had retired from his employment in the ordinary course.`
  line
  line `(6) Where the Managing Director of the Sikkim Bank has, after the 16th day of November, 1976 and`
  line `before the appointed day, been paid any sum by way of compensation or gratuity, the co-operative bank`
  line `shall be entitled to claim refund of any sum so paid if the payment is not confirmed by the State`
  line `Government by general or special order.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (32699)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32699&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any law, other than this Act, or in any decree or order of any court, tribunal or`
  line `other authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (32700)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32700&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or any officer of that Government or the State Government, or`
  line `the co-operative bank or any officer of the State Government or the co-operative bank or other person`
  line `authorised by the Central Government or the State Government or the co-operative bank, for anything`
  line `which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or any officer or other`
  line `employee of that Government or the State Government or the co-operative bank or any officer or other`
  line `employee of the State Government or of the co-operative bank or other person authorised by the State`
  line `Government or the co-operative bank, for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is`
  line `in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (32701)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32701&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Any person who,--`
  line
  line `(a) having in his possession, custody or control any property forming part of the undertakings of`
  line `the Sikkim Bank, wrongfully withholds such property from the Central Government, or the State`
  line `Government or the co-operative bank; or`
  line
  line `(b) wrongfully obtains possession of, or retains, any property forming part of any undertaking of`
  line `the Sikkim Bank or wilfully withholds or fails to furnish to the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government or the co-operative bank, or any person or body of persons specified by that Government`
  line `or the State Government or the co-operative bank, any document relating to such undertaking which`
  line `may be in his possession, custody or control or fails to deliver to the Central Government, or the State`
  line `Government or the co-operative bank or any person or body of persons specified by the Central`
  line `Government or the State Government or the co-operative bank, any assets, books of account, registers`
  line `or other documents in his possession, custody or control, relating to the undertakings of the Sikkim`
  line `Bank; or`
  line
  line `(c) wrongfully removes or destroys any property forming part of any undertaking of the Sikkim`
  line `Bank or prefers any claim under this Act which he knows or has reasonable cause to believe to be`
  line `false or grossly inaccurate,`
  line
  line `shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to ten thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (32702)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32702&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who at the time the offence was committed was in charge of, and was responsible`
  line `to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed`
  line `to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against any punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he had exercised`
  line `all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where any offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary, or other officer shall be deemed to be guilty of`
  line `that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means anybody corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (32703)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32703&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, direct that all or any`
  line `of the powers exercisable by it under this Act, other than the powers conferred by sections 17 and 18, may`
  line `also be exercised by such person or persons as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever any delegation of power is made under sub-section (1), the person to whom such power`
  line `has been delegated shall act under the direction, control and supervision of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (32704)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32704&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified from or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (32705)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32705&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of this`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, remove the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the appointed`
  line day.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (32706)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `References to Sikkim Bank in other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32706&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, any reference to`
  line `Sikkim Bank in any law (other than this Act or the State Bank of Sikkim Proclamation, 1968)or in any`
  line `contract or other instrument shall, except as otherwise provided in any general or special order made by`
  line `the Central Government, be deemed to be a reference to the co-operative bank.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (32707)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Dissolution of Sikkim Bank.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433&sectionId=32707&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00042_198262_1517807325433
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `On the date of the issue of notification under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6, the Sikkim Bank shall stand dissolved, and the State Bank of Sikkim Proclamation, 1968, shall`
  line `stand repealed; and the provisions of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), shall apply`
  line `to such repeal as if the said Proclamation were a Central Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
